import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor

#  
def f(x):
    return np.sin(2 * np.pi * x)

np.random.seed(42)
n_samples = 30
x_true = np.linspace(0, 1, 100)
y_true = f(x_true)

#    
x_train = np.random.rand(n_samples)
y_train = f(x_train) + np.random.normal(0, 0.05, n_samples)

#  
tree = DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=10)
tree.fit(x_train.reshape(-1, 1), y_train)
y_pred_single = tree.predict(x_true.reshape(-1, 1))

# : 100 
B = 100
predictions = []
for _ in range(B):
    idx = np.random.choice(n_samples, size=n_samples, replace=True)  # bootstrap
    x_boot, y_boot = x_train[idx], y_train[idx]
    t = DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=10)
    t.fit(x_boot.reshape(-1, 1), y_boot)
    predictions.append(t.predict(x_true.reshape(-1, 1)))

predictions = np.array(predictions)
y_pred_avg = predictions.mean(axis=0)
y_pred_var = predictions.var(axis=0)

Boosting¶

. .. .

:

boosting- Gradient Boosting.

$L(x,y) = \dfrac{1}{N} \sum^{N}_{i=1} (y_i - a(x_i))^2 \rightarrow min$

k , $a(x) = b_1(x) + b_2(x) + b_3(x) ... + b_k(x)$

.

$b_1(x)$ $s_i^1 = y_i - b_1(x_i)$

$a_2(x_i) = b_1(x_i) + b_2(x_i) = b_1(x_i) + s^1_i = b_1(x_i) + (y_i - b_1(x_i)) = y_i$

$b_2(x) = argmin_{b\in \beta} L(s^1,b(x))$

$s^{k-1}_i = y_i - \sum^{k-1}_{i=1} b_{k-1}(x_i) = y_i -a_{k-1}(x_i)$

$b_k(x) =argmin()_{b\in \beta } L(s^{k-1}, b(x))$

$a_k(x) = a_{k-1}(x) + b_k(x)$
